GERBER GOODNESS: Our foods start with whole ingredients like real fruits, veggies & grains to help nourish your baby right from the start, from infant formula to baby food to snacks and toddler food

body.description: Gerber Lil' Crunchies Mild Cheddar Baked Whole Grain Corn Snacks are a delicious and nutritious snack specially designed for your newly independent eater. Lil' Crunchies snacks are a great first snack for Crawlers because they have a meltable texture that dissolves easily, are easy for them to chew and swallow, and have a shape that is just right for them to pick up. They'll love the delicious flavor. Mild Cheddar Lil' Crunchies snacks have 5 grams of whole grains per serving.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 23, 2023
reviews.reviewText: My son absolutely loves these in fact it's the only flavor of the big puffs he will eat I even like them lol only issue is they go stale SO FAST. You can't leave them out in a bowl for longer than like 15 mins without them starting to get stale. Even in the can after opening they will get stale after a couple days BUT I found the perfect solution for the left over ones in the can put the can in the fridge! It keeps them fresh as a daisy. And this is also a great price

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 27, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Delicious and Nutritious Snack for Your Little Explorer!
reviews.reviewText: As a parent who prioritizes providing nutritious and tasty snacks for my little one, I am delighted to give Gerber Snacks for Baby Lil Crunchies in Mild Cheddar flavor a well-deserved 5-star review! These delightful crunchy treats have become a favorite in our household, and I couldn't be happier with their quality and appeal.Gerber has always been a trusted brand when it comes to baby food, and Lil Crunchies are no exception. The ingredients are carefully selected to ensure they are safe and suitable for little ones. I feel confident that I am offering a wholesome snack that supports my child's growth and development.The Mild Cheddar flavor is an instant hit with my little explorer. It's not too overpowering, making it a perfect introduction to different tastes. The crunchiness adds a fun texture that keeps my child engaged during snack time.The convenient 1.48-ounce pack size is great for on-the-go snacking. Whether we're out for a playdate, on a road trip, or simply at home, the Lil Crunchies are a handy and mess-free snack option.I appreciate that this product comes in a pack of six. It ensures that I always have a stash of Lil Crunchies on hand, so my child never has to miss out on this tasty treat.As a parent, I value the fact that Lil Crunchies contain essential nutrients, including calcium, iron, and vitamin E. These nutrients are crucial for my child's overall well-being, and knowing they are present in this snack gives me peace of mind.The small and easy-to-grab shape of the Lil Crunchies makes it a great option for encouraging self-feeding and fine motor skills in my child. Watching them enjoy their snack independently brings a smile to my face.Lastly, the Lil Crunchies are not only loved by my child but also approved by me. The quality, taste, and nutritional value make them an excellent addition to our snack choices.In conclusion, Gerber Snacks for Baby Lil Crunchies in Mild Cheddar flavor are a delightful and nutritious snack option that I wholeheartedly recommend to all parents. With their baby-friendly ingredients, convenient packaging, and delicious taste, these crunchy treats are a winner in every aspect. Keep your little one happy and nourished with Gerber Lil Crunchies!

reviews.reviewTitle: Babies love the taste but dnt keep for too many days!
reviews.reviewText: Taste is good and it is very crispy in the beginning but you cannot keep open for too long. After few days, it starts to taste stale and oil and sometimes i have to throw away what remains in the tin after few days as my kids refuse to eat what they enjoyed on the first day.
Tastes yummy no wonder my baby likes it. But wonder if it’s a tad too salty for a under-1yo baby..
